results.name: The q expansion of Lambda^5, a Hauptmodul for Gamma_1(5).
comment: Denoted by r^5(tau) by Duke (2005). - _Michael Somos_, Jul 09 2014
reference: A. Erdelyi, Higher Transcendental Functions, McGraw-Hill, 1955, Vol. 3, p. 24.
B. C. Berndt, Ramanujan's Notebooks Part V, Springer-Verlag, see p. 12, Entry 1(ii).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000 (terms 1..1001 from T. D. Noe)
W. Duke, Continued fractions and modular functions, Bull. Amer. Math. Soc. 42 (2005), 137-162. See page 150.
formula: G.f. A(x) = x * B(x)^5 where B(x) is the g.f. of A007325.
G.f. A(q) satisfies 0 = f(A(q), A(q^2)) where f(u,v) = u^2 - v + u*v^3 + u^3*v^2 + 10*u*v * (1 - u + v + u*v). - _Michael Somos_, Mar 09 2004
Given g.f. A(q), then q * A'(q) / A(q) = g.f. of A109064. [Duke (2005)] - _Michael Somos_, Jul 09 2014
mathematica: QP = QPochhammer; s = (QP[q, q^5]*(QP[q^4, q^5]/(QP[q^2, q^5]*QP[q^3, q^5]) ))^5 + O[q]^50; CoefficientList[s, q] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 25 2015, from g.f. of A007325 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<1, 0, A=O(x^n); A = (eta(x + A) / eta(x^5 + A))^6 / x; polcoeff( 2 / (11 + A + sqrt(125 + 22*A + A^2)), n))};

(PARI) {a(n) = local(A, u, v); if( n<0, 0, A=x; for(k=2, n, u = A + x*O(x^k); v = subst(u, x, x^2); A -= x^k * polcoeff( u^2 - v + u*v^3 + u^3*v^2 + 10*u*v * (1 - u + v + u*v), k+1) / 2); polcoeff(A, n))};
